00:39.998 --> 00:42.375
[♪...]

00:46.921 --> 00:50.884
[KIDS LAUGHING]

00:50.967 --> 00:52.802
PLACES, BEES, PLACES.

00:53.094 --> 00:56.264
THIS WEEK...
PICKLING AND PRESERVES.

00:56.514 --> 00:59.100
OH, BOY, SALT JUICE.

00:59.350 --> 01:03.354
{\an5}AMONG THE MOST PRACTICAL
OF THE HONEYBEE BADGES AND
ONE OF MY ALL-TIME "FAVORITOS."

01:03.605 --> 01:05.732
AND NOT A MOMENT TOO SOON.

01:06.065 --> 01:08.985
{\an4}I MEAN, YOU TRY FINDING
A DECENT HALF-SOUR
THIS SIDE OF THE MISSISSIPPI.

01:09.068 --> 01:11.780
[LAUGHING]: ACTUALLY,
I MEAN, DON'T.

01:12.030 --> 01:13.448
'CAUSE YOU CAN'T.

01:13.698 --> 01:15.200
AM I RIGHT, MRS. GIBBONS?

01:15.450 --> 01:17.702
UH, IN A MANNER OF SPEAKING.

01:17.952 --> 01:20.955
BUT WE'LL BE SOLVING THAT LITTLE
PROBLEM TODAY, BEES, WHEN WE...

01:21.039 --> 01:25.293
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:25.543 --> 01:26.836
[CAT YOWLS]

01:26.920 --> 01:28.880
OOH, DUTY CALLS.

01:29.172 --> 01:31.800
M.F. GIBBONS, READY TO DISCOVER
A MORE BEAUTIFUL YOU?

01:32.050 --> 01:33.802
WELL, HI, JANEANE.

01:34.135 --> 01:36.387
OK, I'LL JUST PICK UP
WHERE MRS. GIBBONS LEFT OFF.

01:36.638 --> 01:38.765
[CLEARS THROAT]

01:39.015 --> 01:40.391
A LOT OF PEOPLE DON'T KNOW
PICKLES ARE JUST CUCUMBERS.

01:40.642 --> 01:42.393
I DID, I DO.

01:42.644 --> 01:45.897
UH-HUH, OF COURSE
I CARE ABOUT LIP GLOSS.

01:46.189 --> 01:49.484
{\an5}A FASCINATING FACT:
VINEGAR IS OFTEN USED
IN THE PICKLING PROCESS.

01:49.734 --> 01:52.695
[LAUGHS] I'M SORRY, JANEANE,
I THOUGHT YOU JUST SAID

01:52.946 --> 01:56.491
{\an5}I HAD TO SELL ALL OF
MY PATTY FAYE BEAUTY PRODUCTS
BY THE END OF THE WEEK

01:56.741 --> 01:59.327
OR PATTY FAYE IS GOING TO
REPOSSESS MY COMPANY MINIVAN.

01:59.577 --> 02:02.831
[TRUCK BEEPING]

02:03.122 --> 02:05.416
OH, OH, I SEE.

02:05.667 --> 02:08.169
WOW... WELL, GREAT.

02:08.419 --> 02:09.920
NO PROBLEMO.

02:10.003 --> 02:12.507
WE LOVE A CHALLENGE.

02:12.757 --> 02:16.135
{\an5}TO BE IN A FIX OR A PREDICAMENT
IS OFTEN CALLED
TO BE IN A PICKLE.

02:16.386 --> 02:18.513
NO, JANEANE, THANK <i> YOU...</i>

02:18.763 --> 02:21.933
AND PLEASE TELL SOMEONE
TO TELL SOMEONE TO TELL SOMEONE

02:22.225 --> 02:26.437
TO TELL PATTY FAYE PERSONALLY
THAT SHE CAN COUNT ON ME.

02:26.688 --> 02:30.233
TOODLES.

02:30.483 --> 02:34.696
{\an1}NOW, SEE, ME, I TEND TO ENJOY
A PETIT CORNICHON

02:34.946 --> 02:37.407
{\an1}WHICH IS LIKE THE FRENCH COUSIN
OF THE GHERKIN.

02:37.657 --> 02:39.075
NEWS FLASH, GIRLS.

02:39.158 --> 02:41.870
THAT WAS, UM, HONEYBEE H.Q.

02:42.161 --> 02:44.372
PICKLING'S PUSHED TO NEXT WEEK.

02:44.622 --> 02:47.167
{\an3}OH, MAN, I WAS JUST GETTING TO
pH BALANCES.

02:47.417 --> 02:50.003
YES, WELL, BREAK OUT
YOUR BUSINESS ACUMEN.

02:50.336 --> 02:53.089
WE'RE GOING FOR OUR
YOUNG ENTREPRENEUR BADGES.

02:55.592 --> 02:56.718
[BELL RINGS]

02:59.012 --> 03:00.972
M.F.: ISN'T THIS WONDERFUL?

03:01.222 --> 03:03.433
WHAT BETTER WAY TO LEARN
THAN BY DOING?

03:05.768 --> 03:08.980
{\an3}CAREFUL NOW, YOU DON'T WANT TO
FILL UP BEFORE DINNER.

03:09.272 --> 03:12.275
LET'S KEEP IT MOVING, BEES,
STUFF, STUFF, STUFF.

03:12.525 --> 03:15.278
SELL, SELL, SELL...
THAT'S THE LAST OF 'EM, BOSS.

03:15.528 --> 03:16.988
TERRIF.

03:17.071 --> 03:19.991
BOSS... THAT HAS A NICE RING.

03:20.074 --> 03:22.952
EEKS, LET'S LOSE
THE YELLOW EYE SHADOW, GIRLS.

03:23.244 --> 03:26.205
NOT EVEN I CAN SELL THAT.

03:26.456 --> 03:30.084
{\an1}MOMMY, MY FINGERTIPS
ARE STARTING TO CHAFE.

03:30.168 --> 03:34.088
TIRED...

03:34.172 --> 03:36.132
EXCUSE ME, MRS. GIBBONS?

03:36.215 --> 03:38.343
{\an3}CAN I SUGGEST THAT PORTIA
WEAR GLOVES?

03:38.593 --> 03:41.262
UM, CAN I SUGGEST
YOU DO THE STUFFING?

03:41.512 --> 03:43.514
{\an3}REALLY?

03:43.765 --> 03:46.643
{\an3}I DON'T WANT TO STEAL YOUR SPOT
OR ANYTHING, BUT OK.

03:46.893 --> 03:49.437
[GROANS]

03:49.687 --> 03:51.356
DONE, DONE, DONE, DONE, DONE.

03:51.606 --> 03:54.359
UM, MRS. GIBBONS,
I WAS THINKING...

03:54.609 --> 03:57.862
{\an5}WHAT IF WE TOOK OUT THE FREE
LIPSTICK SAMPLES AND WE ADDED
MORE TISSUE PAPER INSTEAD?

03:58.112 --> 04:00.990
{\an5}I'M SORRY, DEAR,
I KNOW YOUR MOUTH WAS MOVING
AND SOUND CAME OUT

04:01.074 --> 04:03.493
BUT I'M AFRAID I TUNED OUT
EVERYTHING YOU SAID.

04:03.743 --> 04:05.870
{\an5}WELL, THAT WAY YOU CAN JUST
SELL THE FREE LIPSTICKS
ALL BY THEMSELVES

04:06.120 --> 04:08.623
AND THEN YOU CAN
INCREASE YOUR PROFITS.

04:08.873 --> 04:11.668
PLUS, EVERYBODY LOVES
TISSUE PAPER, AM I RIGHT?

04:11.918 --> 04:16.505
SELL THE FREE SAMPLES...

04:16.755 --> 04:18.966
I MEAN, TISSUE PAPER IS AWESOME.

04:19.216 --> 04:21.052
YOU CAN KEEP IT AND REUSE IT FOR
GIFT-WRAPPING OR MAKE A PIÑATA

04:21.427 --> 04:24.013
OR DO ORIGAMI OR PAPIER-MÂCHÉ

04:24.097 --> 04:26.349
OR MAKE A FANCY BLANKET
FOR A MOUSE.

04:26.599 --> 04:28.768
OR FINGER CAN WEAR IT
AS A CAPE.

04:29.018 --> 04:31.854
WHOO, LOOK AT ME, I'M FINGER,
I'M WEARING A FANCY DRESS.

04:32.105 --> 04:34.774
LOVE, LOVE, LOVE
THE IDEA, BESSIE.

04:35.024 --> 04:37.735
GOT ANY MORE?

04:37.986 --> 04:41.197
{\an6}WELL, UM, YOU PROBABLY COULD
GET A LOT MORE STUFF DONE
IF IT WASN'T JUST YOU DOING IT.

04:41.281 --> 04:43.366
YOU KNOW, BESSIE,...

04:43.616 --> 04:46.828
YOU'RE JUST 80 HOURS AWAY FROM
THE YOUNG ENTREPRENEURS BADGE.

04:47.078 --> 04:50.581
{\an1}HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO BE
MY APPRENTICE?

04:50.832 --> 04:53.793
[GASPS] WOW, YOUR
SECOND IN COMMAND?

04:54.043 --> 04:55.420
I'D LOVE IT.

04:55.670 --> 04:57.463
OK, EVERYBODY, GREAT WORK.

04:57.714 --> 04:59.674
...YOU'RE ALL FIRED
EXCEPT FOR BESSIE.

04:59.924 --> 05:01.884
YAY... OH, SORRY, GUYS.

05:02.135 --> 05:04.429
I MEAN, I'M SORRY YOU'RE FIRED,
BUT YAY FOR ME!

05:04.679 --> 05:06.222
[PHONES RINGING...]

05:06.305 --> 05:08.433
[GROANING]

05:08.516 --> 05:10.310
AAH!

05:10.560 --> 05:12.562
WHEE!

05:12.812 --> 05:14.230
[CLEARS THROAT]

05:14.313 --> 05:16.190
UH-HUH, UH-HUH.

05:16.524 --> 05:19.235
WELL, M.F. IS SPREAD
PRETTY THIN, SO... [LAUGHS]

05:19.318 --> 05:23.614
{\an5}OH, I CAN MAKE THAT 4:40
AT 3:45, BUT THAT'LL MEAN
MOVING OUR 1:15 TO 2:30, SO...

05:23.865 --> 05:26.242
YEAH, NOW I'M REALLY
PUSHING IT. [LAUGHS]

05:26.325 --> 05:28.619
NO WORRIES, JANEANE,
WE'RE ON IT, OK?

05:28.870 --> 05:30.496
{\an1}[SCREAMS] WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

05:30.747 --> 05:32.707
MOMMY!

05:32.957 --> 05:34.208
{\an5}[PHONE RINGING]

05:32.957 --> 05:34.208
OOH, I GOTTA TAKE THIS.

05:34.542 --> 05:35.793
[SCREAMS]

05:36.044 --> 05:37.879
M.F. GIBBONS' OFFICE.

05:38.129 --> 05:38.463
{\an1}ARE YOU READY TO DISCOVER
A MORE BEAUTIFUL YOU?

05:41.007 --> 05:43.718
MOMMY, BESSIE'S IN MY ROOM.

05:43.968 --> 05:46.054
CALL THE POLICE.

05:46.304 --> 05:49.432
TRY TO IGNORE HER, DEAR, SHE'S
HELPING MOMMY SELL HER MAKEUP.

05:49.682 --> 05:51.726
{\an3}[STAMMERS]

05:51.976 --> 05:54.520
{\an1}DO YOU WANT TO STUFF ENVELOPES
SO MOMMY CAN KEEP HER VAN?

05:54.771 --> 05:56.397
{\an1}EXACTLY.

05:56.647 --> 05:59.108
{\an1}NOW, WHY DON'T YOU GO
READ A MAGAZINE?

05:59.192 --> 06:00.485
{\an1}[SCREAMS]

06:00.735 --> 06:02.653
OH, HI, MRS. GIBBONS.

06:02.904 --> 06:04.280
I WAS JUST REORGANIZING
YOUR PRESCRIPTIONS.

06:04.363 --> 06:06.074
[GASPS] MRS. GIBBONS...

06:06.365 --> 06:09.494
ENLARGED PORES?

06:09.744 --> 06:13.372
{\an6}HAVE YOU EVER CONSIDERED
PATTY FAYE'S "PORE VOUS"
VANISHING MASK?

06:13.623 --> 06:17.418
{\an6}PATTY FAYE ALWAYS SAYS,
"IF A GAL CAN BE MORE BEAUTIFUL,
YOU SHOULD TELL HER."

06:17.668 --> 06:18.377
{\an3}RIGHT?

06:22.840 --> 06:23.591
[MUFFLED]: RIGHT.

06:28.054 --> 06:30.014
{\an3}DOUBLE CAFF EXTRA FOAM,
JUST HOW YOU LIKE IT, M.F.

06:30.264 --> 06:31.516
WELL, IT ALL ADDS UP.

06:31.766 --> 06:33.810
HOORAY FOR THIS QUARTER.

06:34.060 --> 06:38.397
NOW, IF I'M NOT MISTAKEN,
SOMEONE HAS A TENNIS LESSON.

06:38.648 --> 06:41.275
[SIGHING]: OH, HOW I HATE
TO ABANDON MY WORK.

06:41.567 --> 06:43.152
{\an3}IT WAS GONNA BE
A SURPRISE, BUT...

06:43.486 --> 06:44.946
I CAN'T WAIT, IT'S SO GOOD.

06:45.196 --> 06:46.489
YOU'RE GONNA BE SO EXCITED.

06:46.739 --> 06:48.616
I CLEARED YOUR WHOLE CALENDAR.

06:48.866 --> 06:52.036
NOW YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO
ANYTHING TODAY BUT WORK.

06:52.286 --> 06:53.704
ISN'T THAT GREAT?

06:53.955 --> 06:55.164
[PHONE BUZZING]

06:55.248 --> 06:57.291
FAB.

06:57.375 --> 06:59.335
{\an3}OH, PROBABLY JUST ANOTHER
BEAUTY EMERGENCY.

06:59.418 --> 07:02.004
{\an3}OUR WORK IS NEVER DONE,
AM I RIGHT? [LAUGHS]

07:02.255 --> 07:03.172
{\an6}M.F. GIBBONS' OFFICE,
ARE YOU READY TO DISCOVER
A MORE BEAUTIFUL YOU?

07:03.256 --> 07:04.966
MOMMY...

07:05.216 --> 07:07.343
HUNGRY...

07:07.426 --> 07:09.303
[STOMACHS GROWLING]

07:09.387 --> 07:11.097
{\an3}OOH, I'M FEELING
A LITTLE PECKISH MYSELF.

07:11.347 --> 07:13.182
LUNCH.

07:13.266 --> 07:16.060
{\an3}Bessie: LUNCH... [LAUGHS]
GOOD ONE, LADIES.

07:16.310 --> 07:17.520
BUT WE'RE NOT GONNA
HAVE TIME FOR LUNCH.

07:17.770 --> 07:19.856
M.F. IS RUNNING WAY BEHIND.

07:20.106 --> 07:21.107
WITH ALL THIS, I HAD TO
PUSH LUNCH BACK TO THIS WEEKEND.

07:21.440 --> 07:23.067
BUT GOOD NEWS- JERKY?

07:29.574 --> 07:30.658
[GRUNTING...]

07:33.077 --> 07:33.578
[GRUNTS]

07:46.549 --> 07:48.551
M.F. GIBBONS HERE.

07:48.801 --> 07:51.220
I UNDERSTAND YOU HAVE
SOME QUESTIONS ABOUT ROUGE.

07:51.304 --> 07:52.555
{\an5}OH...

07:51.304 --> 07:52.555
[PHONE RINGING]

07:52.889 --> 07:54.015
Bessie: PEGGY LIU RETURNING.

07:54.265 --> 07:55.808
PEGS, M.F. HERE.

07:56.058 --> 07:57.143
{\an5}SO THE MASCARA IS...

07:56.058 --> 07:57.143
[PHONE RINGING]

07:57.560 --> 07:58.728
Bessie: NANCY YOUNG, YOUR 12:16.

07:58.978 --> 08:00.229
OH, NANCY, HOW...

08:00.313 --> 08:01.397
Bessie: IT'S YOUR 12:17.

08:01.647 --> 08:02.732
YOUR 12:18.

08:02.982 --> 08:05.109
12:18-1/2.

08:05.359 --> 08:06.402
I'D HURRY, SHE'S BEEN HOLDING
FOR, LIKE, TWO SECONDS.

08:06.694 --> 08:06.944
[YELLING, PHONES RINGING]

08:09.614 --> 08:13.284
{\an4}YOU'VE GOT A PRETTY FULL SLATE
THIS AFTERNOON, SO LET'S
MAKE IT A NUMBER ONE, K?

08:13.576 --> 08:16.412
{\an3}OK, BESSIE... I'LL JUST BE
A MINUTE. [SCREAMS]

08:16.495 --> 08:18.581
55 SECONDS, YOU HAVE 55 SECONDS.

08:18.831 --> 08:20.499
MAYBE I CAN...

08:20.750 --> 08:22.543
{\an3}HOLD IT?
NO, I WOULDN'T ADVISE THAT.

08:22.793 --> 08:23.753
{\an3}THE HUMAN BLADDER IS
A VERY DELICATE THING.

08:24.003 --> 08:26.214
[SCREAMS]

08:26.464 --> 08:28.424
[SIGHS]

08:28.507 --> 08:29.550
T.P.?

08:29.800 --> 08:31.385
[STAMMERS]

08:33.929 --> 08:37.265
[WHINES] MY BLOOD SUGAR...

08:37.350 --> 08:38.433
{\an3}SOUP'S ON.

08:38.517 --> 08:39.559
FINALLY.

08:39.809 --> 08:41.020
YUMMERS.

08:41.270 --> 08:43.272
WHAT ARE WE HAVING?

08:43.356 --> 08:45.191
{\an3}LOBSTER BISQUE, STEAK-WICHES,
AND APPLE COBBLER.

08:45.524 --> 08:47.068
OOH, SOMETHING FOR EVERYONE.

08:47.318 --> 08:48.569
{\an1}<i>TRES BIEN.</i>

08:48.819 --> 08:51.447
[FOOD PROCESSOR WHIRRING]

08:55.493 --> 08:56.786
PRE-CHEWED TO SAVE TIME.

08:57.036 --> 08:58.412
[RETCHING]

08:58.496 --> 09:02.416
[SHIVERING]

09:02.500 --> 09:06.629
{\an1}BESSIE, DEAR... I'VE GOT
A VERY IMPORTANT JOB FOR YOU.

09:06.879 --> 09:09.966
REMEMBER THOSE
YELLOW EYE SHADOWS?

09:10.216 --> 09:12.593
[INSECTS BUZZING]

09:17.306 --> 09:20.351
AH, I LOVE THE DUMP.

09:20.434 --> 09:24.647
{\an5}SEEMS LIKE A WASTE TO THROW OUT
ALL THIS PERFECTLY
GLAMOROUS EYE SHADOW.

09:24.897 --> 09:28.484
BUT M.F. DIDN'T BUILD AN EMPIRE
ON BAD DECISIONS, SO...

09:28.567 --> 09:29.777
[BUZZING...]

09:33.281 --> 09:33.781
[GASPS]

09:37.576 --> 09:39.787
THANK GOODNESS WE ESCAPED.

09:40.037 --> 09:42.331
WHEN ARE YOU GONNA
GET RID OF HER, MOMMY?

09:48.087 --> 09:51.882
[LAUGHING]

09:52.133 --> 09:54.468
WHAT ON EARTH?

09:52.133 --> 09:54.468
[GASPS]

09:54.802 --> 09:56.804
SO IT'S 25 CENTS
FOR THE MAKEOVER

09:57.054 --> 09:59.223
AND 50 CENTS IF YOU WANT TO
TAKE THE EYE SHADOW HOME.

09:59.473 --> 10:03.102
THANK YOU, YES, YOU'RE WELCOME,
PLEASE SEE THE CASHIER.

10:03.352 --> 10:07.064
{\an6}HI, ARE YOU READY
TO DISCOVER THE BEAUTIFUL...
OH, HI, MRS. GIBBONS.

10:07.315 --> 10:08.441
ISN'T THIS GREAT?

10:08.691 --> 10:10.526
A GREAT BIG MESS.

10:10.609 --> 10:13.529
AREN'T THEY GLAMOROUS?

10:13.612 --> 10:15.865
VOILA-LA.

10:16.115 --> 10:18.993
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM,
YOU ARE FIRED.

10:19.243 --> 10:22.371
{\an4}I AM PERSONALLY GOING TO
TELL SOMEONE TO TELL SOMEONE
TO TELL SOMEONE

10:22.663 --> 10:25.958
{\an1}TO WRITE A STRONG LETTER
TO PATTY FAYE HERSELF.

10:26.208 --> 10:29.628
Woman: WHY DON'T YOU
JUST TELL ME?

10:29.879 --> 10:31.839
[STAMMERS] JANEANE...

10:32.089 --> 10:34.550
I... I... I...

10:34.842 --> 10:39.555
{\an6}I, I, I HEARD FROM SOMEONE
WHO TOLD SOMEONE WHO TOLD
PATTY FAYE PERSONALLY

10:39.639 --> 10:42.308
THAT WE HAD A JUNIOR
SALES REP DOWN HERE

10:42.641 --> 10:45.978
MAKING LEMONS OUT OF LEMONADE.

10:46.228 --> 10:49.815
{\an1}OH... I TAUGHT HER
EVERYTHING SHE KNOWS.

10:50.066 --> 10:55.154
{\an4}IN FACT, I WOULD LIKE TO PRESENT
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM WITH
A YOUNG ENTREPRENEUR'S BADGE.

10:55.404 --> 10:58.616
WELL, GOOD ON YOU, M.F.,
BECAUSE PATTY FAYE WOULD LIKE TO

10:58.866 --> 11:02.244
PASS THE KEYS TO THE COMPANY VAN
FROM YOU TO HER.

11:02.495 --> 11:05.414
IT'S ALL YOURS, BESSIE.

11:05.498 --> 11:09.251
[ENGINE REVS]

11:09.502 --> 11:11.295
HA, WOW.

11:11.545 --> 11:14.006
[STAMMERING]

11:14.256 --> 11:17.593
BUT SHE CAN'T EVEN DRIVE.

11:17.676 --> 11:18.886
GOOD POINT, I THINK
I'LL DONATE IT.

11:22.515 --> 11:24.183
[ENGINE REVS]

11:28.646 --> 11:32.608
{\an3}SO, M.F., ABOUT YOUR
SALES NUMBERS...

11:36.695 --> 11:38.864
[♪...]

11:52.002 --> 11:54.422
{\an1}UGH, TAN ON TAN,
WHAT AM I THINKING?

11:54.713 --> 11:57.633
TOO MATCHY-MATCHY,
NO ONE LIKES A SHOW-OFF.

11:57.716 --> 12:00.010
PERFECT, I'M DEFINITELY
A WINTER.

12:00.261 --> 12:02.888
Man: Is your dog a heftier
shadow of his former self?

12:03.139 --> 12:06.308
{\an5}Does he laze around eating
snacks all day and watching
commercials like this one?

12:06.559 --> 12:09.395
Is he too lethargic to even
reach for the remote control?

12:09.728 --> 12:12.231
{\an5}Your dog could be headed for
serious health problems
and a shorter lifespan.

12:16.569 --> 12:18.237
Don't you want your dog
to live longer?

12:18.487 --> 12:19.655
Don't you care?

12:28.581 --> 12:32.668
MY SAUSAGE MAKING BADGE,
I'VE BEEN LOOKING FOR THIS.

12:32.751 --> 12:35.212
OH, HAPPY, HOW DID I LET YOU
LET YOURSELF GO?

12:35.463 --> 12:37.423
[BELCH]

12:37.798 --> 12:40.593
A responsible pet owner chooses
rigorous exercise and Vegi Pup.

12:40.926 --> 12:43.846
I'M SORRY, BOY,
I'M GONNA MAKE THIS UP TO YOU.

12:43.929 --> 12:45.306
[SNORING]

12:45.556 --> 12:47.516
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

12:47.600 --> 12:50.352
WITNESS THE FITNESS.

12:50.603 --> 12:52.605
[WHIMPERING]

12:52.855 --> 12:54.690
{\an1}TUCK THAT BELLY IN,
WORK THAT CORE.

12:54.940 --> 12:56.859
KEEP IT TIGHT.

12:57.109 --> 12:59.278
LOOKING GOOD.

13:15.252 --> 13:17.713
[WHIMPERS]

13:17.796 --> 13:18.631
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

13:18.881 --> 13:20.716
[YELPS]

13:20.799 --> 13:22.635
STAY STRONG, HIGGENBOTTOM.

13:22.927 --> 13:25.221
HOW MANY TIMES CAN WE
HAVE THIS CONVERSATION?

13:25.471 --> 13:27.348
FRESH COOKIES ARE
A HEALTH DON'T.

13:27.598 --> 13:29.308
HAVE AN APPLE.

13:29.558 --> 13:30.684
[SCOFFS] JUST GIVE HIM
A COOKIE, MESSY.

13:31.018 --> 13:33.103
NO ONE WANTS TO HEAR THIS.

13:33.354 --> 13:35.189
PORTIA, I TOO USED TO BELIEVE
THAT TREATS WERE LOVE

13:35.439 --> 13:37.149
BUT THERE'S NOTHING LIKE
THE GIFT OF HEALTH.

13:37.399 --> 13:38.567
{\an1}I JUST READ A FASCINATING
CLINICAL STUDY...

13:38.901 --> 13:40.945
NO WAY, SHE'S STILL TALKING.

13:41.195 --> 13:43.531
...HEARTWORMS,
AND, YIKES, BAD BREATH.

13:43.781 --> 13:46.534
HEY, HAPPY,
WHO'S A BIG, LAZY DOG?

13:46.867 --> 13:48.410
WHO'S GOOD FOR NOTHING?

13:48.661 --> 13:50.704
WHO IS HE, WHO IS HE...

13:50.955 --> 13:52.623
COME HERE.

13:52.915 --> 13:55.376
Bessie: HAPPY WALTER
HIGGENBOTTOM, STAY.

13:55.626 --> 13:57.169
[BARKS]

13:57.419 --> 13:59.588
PORTIA, AS A PET OWNER
WHO CARES

13:59.672 --> 14:02.591
I MUST INSIST
THAT HAPPY NOT EAT THAT COOKIE.

14:02.675 --> 14:04.093
OK, SO LET'S REVIEW.

14:04.343 --> 14:06.762
ONE, YOU ARE NOT THE BOSS OF ME.

14:06.845 --> 14:11.350
{\an5}AND B, IT'S NOT MY FAULT
IF YOUR DOG LISTENS TO ME
INSTEAD OF YOU, OK?

14:11.600 --> 14:13.936
HAPPY... COOKIE.

14:14.186 --> 14:17.189
YUMMY... OR WHATEVER.

14:17.439 --> 14:18.774
COME HERE, BOY, NOW.

14:18.857 --> 14:20.234
[SCOFFS] "BOY"?

14:20.484 --> 14:22.027
HE HAS A NAME, BESSIE.

14:22.278 --> 14:23.779
DON'T YOU, HAPPY?

14:23.862 --> 14:26.782
COME ON, YOU KNOW YOU WANT IT.

14:29.410 --> 14:31.120
{\an1}[WHIMPERS]

14:31.370 --> 14:32.580
DON'T YOU EAT
THAT COOKIE, MISTER.

14:32.830 --> 14:33.956
[WHIMPERING...]

14:43.132 --> 14:45.092
[GASPS] HAPPY...

14:45.342 --> 14:46.635
I THINK WE NEED TO
TALK ABOUT THIS IN PRIVATE.

14:46.719 --> 14:48.512
LET'S JOG HOME.

14:52.850 --> 14:55.352
SO THAT'S HOW IT IS.

14:55.603 --> 14:57.771
{\an5}OH, YEAH, SURE, I MEAN,
FORGET THE FACT THAT
I RESCUED YOU FROM THE STREETS.

14:57.855 --> 15:00.149
[GROWLS]

15:00.399 --> 15:02.526
WELL, I'M SORRY
TO HEAR YOU SAY THAT.

15:02.776 --> 15:05.195
IF PORTIA'S SO WONDERFUL,
WHY DON'T YOU GO LIVE WITH HER?

15:05.446 --> 15:06.614
[SNARLING]

15:06.905 --> 15:09.658
WELL, THAT'S DANDY.

15:09.742 --> 15:12.536
{\an5}LEAVE THEN, AND DON'T LOOK BACK,
'CAUSE I WON'T BE HERE,
I CAN ASSURE YOU OF THAT.

15:12.786 --> 15:14.204
WHAT CAN I SAY?

15:14.455 --> 15:16.373
HE KNOWS I'M RAD.

15:16.624 --> 15:20.044
WATCH, HE'LL COME CRAWLING BACK
IN NO TIME.

15:20.294 --> 15:22.755
[INSECTS CHIRPING...]

15:33.891 --> 15:36.560
{\an1}SO LISTEN, TOO BAD
ABOUT HAPPY AND EVERYTHING

15:36.810 --> 15:40.648
{\an5}BUT NOW YOU CAN SPEND
A LITTLE QUALITY TIME WITH
YOUR FUTURE SIDEKICK... ME.

15:40.939 --> 15:42.650
THANKS, BEN...

15:42.900 --> 15:44.860
BUT IT'S NOT THE SAME.

15:44.943 --> 15:47.571
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,
YOU'RE A GOOD KID...

15:47.821 --> 15:49.698
BUT HAPPY...

15:49.782 --> 15:51.992
HAPPY WAS MY DOG.

15:57.790 --> 16:00.959
[PANTING]

16:01.210 --> 16:03.879
"TODAY'S BLIND ITEM...

16:03.962 --> 16:06.757
{\an5}"WHAT BEAUTIFUL BLONDE HONEYBEE
HAS BEEN SIGHTED AT
ALL THE RIGHT PLACES

16:07.049 --> 16:09.718
"WITH A NEW BLUE B.F.F.?

16:10.052 --> 16:13.555
HE MAY BE A DOG, BUT THESE FAST
FRIENDS ARE THE CAT'S MEOW."

16:13.806 --> 16:16.183
OH, HAPPY... HOW COULD YOU?

16:16.433 --> 16:18.686
MY OWN DOG... [SOBS]

16:18.936 --> 16:20.604
IS NO BOND SACRED?

16:20.854 --> 16:23.065
[SOBBING]

16:23.315 --> 16:25.025
OH, BEN, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

16:25.275 --> 16:27.403
NOW MY FACE SMELLS LIKE BOY.

16:27.653 --> 16:30.406
{\an3}I'M COMFORTING YOU, THAT'S
WHAT MAN'S BEST FRIEND DOES.

16:30.656 --> 16:32.199
WOOF.

16:32.449 --> 16:33.701
{\an1}DON'T SAY "WOOF"...
IT'S TOO SOON.

16:39.248 --> 16:40.749
[SOFT LAUGHTER]

16:40.833 --> 16:42.042
HAPPY LEFT BESSIE.

16:50.843 --> 16:51.093
WHA...

16:56.181 --> 16:57.558
[PORTIA LAUGHING]

16:57.808 --> 16:58.600
[CAMERA SNAPPING]

17:05.983 --> 17:07.108
Bessie: OH!

17:09.194 --> 17:10.194
[LAUGHS]

17:13.115 --> 17:16.034
[BARKING, CHOKING]

17:16.285 --> 17:18.829
[PANTING]

17:19.163 --> 17:22.249
Portia: MY PROBLEM IS
I'M ALWAYS THINKING OF OTHERS.

17:22.499 --> 17:24.792
LIKE I THINK THAT LADY
SHOULDN'T WEAR CAPRIS.

17:24.877 --> 17:26.878
IT CUTS HER OFF, I MEAN...

17:27.212 --> 17:30.257
{\an3}EVERYONE THINKS I HAVE ALL
THE ANSWERS, AND, LIKE, I DON'T.

17:30.507 --> 17:31.842
I MEAN, I BARELY READ.

17:35.220 --> 17:37.306
[BEN PANTING...]

17:44.897 --> 17:46.774
[SIGHS] WELL...

17:47.024 --> 17:52.112
IF HAPPY'S HAPPY,
THEN I'M HAPPY.

17:52.362 --> 17:54.072
COME ON, BEN.

17:54.323 --> 17:56.784
I TOLD YOU,
MY DOG NAME IS PIZZA.

17:57.034 --> 17:58.660
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?

17:58.911 --> 18:01.371
HUH?

18:01.622 --> 18:03.707
{\an5}UGH, GET YOUR FLEA-RIDDEN
CARCASS OFF THAT COUCH
BEFORE WE HAVE TO BURN IT.

18:03.957 --> 18:05.793
NOW SHOO, SHOO.

18:06.043 --> 18:08.128
WELCOME TO THE CIVILIZED WORLD.

18:08.378 --> 18:12.466
{\an5}UGH... THIS IS KIND OF
A LOT OF DRAMA JUST TO
PLAY WITH MESSY'S MIND.

18:15.344 --> 18:17.679
ALL RIGHT, GOOD FETCH, PIZZA.

18:17.930 --> 18:18.889
{\an1}YOU READY?

18:19.181 --> 18:22.643
GO... HOME... NOW.

18:22.893 --> 18:25.479
{\an1}NOT YET, BUDDY,
ONE MORE, ONE MORE.

18:25.729 --> 18:28.398
{\an1}GO GET IT.

18:28.482 --> 18:29.566
{\an1}GOOD BOY.

18:29.817 --> 18:31.777
[QUACKING]

18:32.027 --> 18:34.029
HAPPY, THIS IS MY BATHROOM.

18:34.112 --> 18:35.823
YOUR BATHROOM IS THE BACKYARD.

18:36.073 --> 18:37.825
[TOILET FLUSHES]

18:38.158 --> 18:39.910
FINALLY... I HOPE YOU KEPT
YOUR PAWS OFF MY PRODUCTS.

18:39.993 --> 18:42.037
[SCREAMS]

18:42.120 --> 18:44.790
YOU'VE CONTAMINATED
EVERYTHING I CARE ABOUT!

18:45.040 --> 18:46.875
{\an1}[BARKING]

18:46.959 --> 18:49.753
LISTEN, FUR BAG,
YOU'RE LUCKY I TOOK YOU IN.

18:51.505 --> 18:53.257
[BARKING]

18:53.507 --> 18:56.051
{\an3}UH, YOU NEED TO
WORK ON YOUR VOCAB.

18:56.134 --> 18:58.053
{\an1}[YELPS]

18:58.345 --> 19:00.806
NO ONE WALKS OUT
ON PORTIA GIBBONS.

19:02.975 --> 19:05.477
{\an1}[SNARLING]

19:05.727 --> 19:07.813
DUH, THE COLLAR IS WIRED.

19:08.063 --> 19:10.232
TAKE ONE STEP OUT THE DOOR,
YOU'LL GET SHOCKED AGAIN.

19:16.989 --> 19:19.908
OH... OH, POLYESTER...

19:20.158 --> 19:22.703
ACETATE...

19:29.042 --> 19:32.921
[WHIMPERING]

19:33.255 --> 19:34.256
Portia: NICE TRY, GENIUS.

19:34.506 --> 19:36.425
[YELPS]

19:36.675 --> 19:38.427
{\an3}I TOLD YOU, NO ONE WALKS OUT
ON PORTIA GIBBONS.

19:41.221 --> 19:42.848
LOOK, PIZZA, BALL.

19:43.098 --> 19:44.308
I'M TAKING FIVE.

19:44.558 --> 19:46.602
PIZZA BREAK.

19:46.852 --> 19:49.229
BALL, BALL, BALL, BALL, BALL,
COME ON, PLAYTIME, PIZZA.

19:49.479 --> 19:51.982
BALL, BALL, BALL,
BALL, BALL, BALL, BALL...

19:52.065 --> 19:55.193
BALL, BEN, BALL, BALL, BEN, BEN,
BEN, BALL, BALL, BALL...

19:55.444 --> 19:57.029
BEN, BEN, BALL, BALL,
BEN, BEN, BALL, BALL...

19:57.279 --> 19:58.822
[SCREAMS]

19:59.072 --> 20:01.867
NO WONDER HAPPY LEFT YOU.

20:02.117 --> 20:04.953
WHAT... DID... YOU... SAY?

20:05.245 --> 20:07.247
YOU'RE NO FUN ANYMORE.

20:07.497 --> 20:10.459
GUESS WHAT... THERE'S MORE
TO LIFE THAN WORKING OUT.

20:10.709 --> 20:14.671
{\an5}IF I DIDN'T HAVE
SUCH A SWEET DEAL WITH MOM,
I'D GO LIVE WITH PORTIA TOO.

20:14.922 --> 20:19.051
{\an5}PIZZA... SO THAT'S THE THANKS
I GET FOR LETTING YOU
BE MY SUBSTITUTE DOG.

20:19.343 --> 20:22.554
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE US.

20:22.804 --> 20:24.431
{\an3}I KNOW... WELL,
HOW CAN YOU JUDGE ME?

20:24.681 --> 20:25.974
{\an3}I'M UNDER A LOT OF
PRESSURE HERE.

20:26.058 --> 20:28.018
I, I GET THAT, I...

20:28.101 --> 20:30.062
{\an3}WELL, FINGER AND I HAVE
DISCUSSED THE MATTER

20:30.312 --> 20:32.397
{\an3}AND HE HAS HELPED ME SEE...
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:32.648 --> 20:35.108
I CAN BE A LITTLE BOSSY.

20:35.192 --> 20:37.945
I SAID IT FIRST,
HE JUST AGREED WITH ME.

20:38.195 --> 20:40.530
YEAH, BUT FINGER JUST HAS
A WAY OF PUTTING THINGS.

20:43.241 --> 20:45.160
WHAT DO YOU WANT, MESSY?

20:45.243 --> 20:46.995
YOU'VE GOTTA LET ME
TALK TO HAPPY.

20:47.079 --> 20:48.705
HE DOESN'T WANT TO
SEE YOU... EVER.

20:48.956 --> 20:50.123
THAT CAN'T BE TRUE.

20:50.457 --> 20:52.542
JUST LET ME TALK TO HIM, PLEASE.

20:52.793 --> 20:54.878
FINE... HAPPY, COME TELL MESSY
YOU CAN'T STAND HER.

20:55.128 --> 20:57.089
I MEAN, HAPPY...

20:57.381 --> 20:59.216
YOU'RE SUCH A GOOD BOY.

20:59.466 --> 21:01.677
[WHIMPERING]

21:01.927 --> 21:03.929
{\an1}AH, SHH, SHH...
DON'T SPEAK.

21:04.179 --> 21:06.306
{\an1}I KNOW IT'S MY FAULT, AND,
HAPPY, I JUST WANTED TO SAY...

21:06.556 --> 21:08.100
{\an5}Portia: WRITE IT IN A LETTER.

21:06.556 --> 21:08.100
[DOOR SLAMS]

21:08.475 --> 21:10.769
GIVE IT, THAT'S
MY MOM'S LIPSTICK.

21:11.019 --> 21:11.979
[WHIMPERING]

21:14.940 --> 21:17.067
202?

21:17.359 --> 21:21.196
{\an1}WAIT A MINUTE,
THAT'S S.O.S. BACKWARDS.

21:21.279 --> 21:23.532
WE GOTTA BREAK HIM OUT.

21:23.782 --> 21:25.784
PIZZA, YOU CREATE A DISTRACTION
WHILE I GO IN THROUGH THE BACK.

21:26.034 --> 21:28.203
[BEN HOWLS]

21:28.286 --> 21:29.621
HAPPY!

21:29.871 --> 21:31.164
WHERE ARE YOU?

21:31.456 --> 21:32.958
ANSWER ME, PLEASE.

21:33.208 --> 21:35.127
[BEN BARKING]

21:35.377 --> 21:38.046
{\an3}UGH, WELL, THE HIGGENBOTTOM
BOY'S DERANGED.

21:38.130 --> 21:39.423
MARCO!

21:39.673 --> 21:40.674
Happy [HOWLING]: POLO!

21:40.924 --> 21:41.883
MARCO!

21:42.134 --> 21:43.051
{\an3}POLO!

21:43.135 --> 21:44.219
MARCO!

21:44.302 --> 21:45.971
{\an3}POLO!

21:48.724 --> 21:51.226
{\an1}NOW AREN'T YOU GLAD
I TAUGHT YOU MARCO POLO?

21:51.476 --> 21:54.980
{\an3}[GASPING]

21:55.230 --> 21:57.107
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING,
STINKENBOTTOM?

21:57.441 --> 22:00.235
HE'S MY DOG, PORTIA,
AND WE'RE GOING HOME TOGETHER.

22:00.318 --> 22:03.321
YOU'RE NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

22:03.572 --> 22:05.615
[SCREAMS]

22:05.866 --> 22:08.994
THOSE ARE 14-CARAT CUBIC
ZIRCONIA, YOU CLASSLESS MUTT.

22:12.330 --> 22:14.875
{\an1}HAPPY, I LOVE YOU
JUST THE WAY YOU ARE.

22:15.125 --> 22:17.044
I JUST WANTED YOU TO BE HEALTHY.

22:17.294 --> 22:19.504
BUT YOU CAN BE ANY SIZE.

22:19.755 --> 22:21.923
YOU WANT ME TO CARRY YOU
THE REST OF THE WAY HOME?

22:22.174 --> 22:24.217
[BARKS]

22:22.174 --> 22:24.217
YOU MEAN IT?

22:24.301 --> 22:25.927
BOY, FOR A LAZY DOG,
YOU CAN SURE PICK UP THE PACE.

22:26.178 --> 22:28.180
WAIT UP!

22:28.513 --> 22:31.266
HELLO, BESSIE, HAPPY?

22:31.349 --> 22:32.476
WOOF?

22:34.227 --> 22:37.064
[♪...]

23:14.226 --> 23:15.560
[KIDS LAUGHING...]
